paragraphs.text:
%md
## End to End Machine learning workflow on Oracle Autonomous Data Warehouse (ADW)

### A Notebook that shows how one can run the entire data science pipeline and also deploy the model for the new data.
#### The data used is related with direct marketing campaigns of a Portuguese banking institution.The marketing campaigns were based on phone calls. Often, more than one contact to the same client was required,in order to access if the product (bank term deposit) would be (or not) subscribed. 
#### By Ravi Panga, April 2019

paragraphs.title: Prediction for new data

paragraphs.text:
%md
 ### The model says that when a person with an Age of 36 with a secondary educational qualification and has a housing loan is 7.74% probably subscribes for a term deposit.
 #### You can also do a batch wise prediction with a table full of customer details by using apply function like we used for the test dataset. However, you can also run it from your remote PC by connecting to ADW with SQL developer, [Python, Node.js and other scripting languages.](https://docs.oracle.com/en/cloud/paas/autonomous-data-warehouse-cloud/user/connecting-nodejs.html#GUID-AB1E323A-65B9-47C4-840B-EC3453F3AD53)

msg.data:
The model says that when a person with an Age of 36 with a secondary educational qualification and has a housing loan is 7.74% probably subscribes for a term deposit.

You can also do a batch wise prediction with a table full of customer details by using apply function like we used for the test dataset. However, you can also run it from your remote PC by connecting to ADW with SQL developer, Python, Node.js and other scripting languages.
